According to Section 13 of the Lagos Tenancy Law 2011, when there is no stipulation as to the notice to be given by either party to determine the tenancy, the following shall apply:

(a) A week’s notice for a tenant at will;
(b) One (1) month’s notice for a monthly tenant;
(c) Three (3) months notice for a quarterly tenant;
(d) Three (3) months notice for a half-yearly tenant; and
(e) Six months notice for a yearly tenant.

Since you are a monthly tenant, your landlord is required to give you a one-month notice before attempting to evict you. If your landlord fails to provide this notice, you can file a claim by way of summons as in Form TL6A and B for recovery of possession, either against your landlord or against any other person refusing to vacate, in the Magisterial District or High Court Division where the premises is situated.

[Act, s.13]

