According to Section 20 of the Nigeria Tax Act 2025, you are allowed to claim deductions for expenses wholly and exclusively incurred in producing income, including:

* Any sum payable by way of interest on debt employed in generating the income of the trade, business, profession or vocation (Section 20(1)(a));
* Rent and premiums, incurred during that period, in respect of land or building occupied for the purposes of generating the income (Section 20(1)(b));
* Any outlay or expenses incurred in respect of:
	+ Salary, wages or other remuneration paid to employees, and cost to the company of any benefit or allowance provided to its employees (Section 20(1)(c)(i) and (ii));
	+ Repair of premises, plant, machinery or fixtures employed in acquiring the income, or for the renewals, repair or alteration of any implement, utensil or articles so employed (Section 20(1)(d));
* Any amount of expenditure incurred for establishing, preserving or defending title to or rights over an asset (Section 20(1)(e));
* Any contribution to any staff pension, provident or other retirement benefits fund, society or scheme approved under the Pension Reform Act or any similar enactment in Nigeria (Section 20(1)(f));
* Any expense proven to the satisfaction of the relevant tax authority to have been incurred, being damage to, or loss of stock or inventory of the trade, business, profession or vocation (Section 20(1)(g));
* Bad or doubtful debts incurred in the course of a trade or business, notwithstanding that the debts were due and payable before the commencement of the basis period (Section 20(1)(h)(i) and (ii));
* Any expense incurred by the trade, business, profession or vocation on research and development for the period (Section 20(1)(h)(iii));
* Any other expense incurred during any previous period for the purpose of such trade or business, or specifically for the period which the profits are being ascertained, provided that any expenditure incurred within six years prior to the commencement of the basis period (Section 20(1)(h)(iv));

Please note that these deductions are subject to specific conditions and limitations outlined in various subsections and schedules of the Nigeria Tax Act 2025.

